definitions.definition: Loud ; shrill , piercing , high- pitched ; rough -sounding.
examples: The trumpet sounded strident against the string orchestra.
The artist chose a strident mixture of colors.

definitions.definition: Forceful (typically in a negative way) or obtrusive .
Vigorous ; making strides ; forceful in a positive way.
